# ChromaIntel Continuation Plan

This file is the autonomous backlog. Work top-down. Mark an item done only after code/docs/artifacts are updated, verification passes, and the milestone is committed.

## Current Baseline

- Repo is public at `https://github.com/namzhale/chromaintel`.
- Latest major implemented layer: public RT fixture adapters, canonical registry docs, enrichment fixtures, method-conditioned evaluation, and optional graph/transformer stubs.
- Current verified tests after the expanded data/model slice: `77 passed` with project `.venv`.
- Current trained demo artifact exists locally at `data/processed/models/trained_forward_bundle.joblib`; the expanded artifact is too large for normal git commits and should stay local until an artifact/LFS policy exists.
- Current expanded local training matrix is 213,941 rows and 202,834 compounds after ReTiNA, METLIN SMRT Figshare, RepoRT, MCMRT, and mock/internal seed assembly; quality target still provisional.
- Current direct-target readiness: measured RT is trainable; quality and risk labels are provisional proxies; asymmetry, tailing, peak widths, resolution, S/N, peak area, and peak height are schema-ready but still need internal or curated measured labels.
- Current inverse recommendation ML baseline exists locally as a proxy-trained reranker; metrics are diagnostic because labels are synthetic suitability proxies, not real accepted/failed assay outcomes.
- Large generated local artifacts are intentionally dirty/uncommitted unless explicitly staged through an artifact workflow: `data/processed/master_dataset.csv`, `data/processed/model_matrix.csv`, and `data/processed/models/trained_forward_bundle.joblib`.

## Milestone A: Data Expansion And Canonical Ingestion

- [x] Add additional reviewed public RT sample imports beyond RepoRT dataset 0001.
- [x] Add a public-source manifest with source name, URL, license, expected fields, adapter status, and known missingness.
- [x] Extend local public import tests for CSV, TSV, JSON/JSONL, and XLSX where dependencies allow.
- [x] Add a canonical merge command that can combine multiple processed external samples with internal/mock data.
- [x] Preserve full provenance for every external row.

## Milestone B: Internal Lab Onboarding Maturity

- [x] Add `docs/internal_lab_onboarding.md` with realistic BE workflow instructions.
- [x] Add template examples for accepted, failed, low intensity, poor resolution, and carryover cases.
- [x] Add validation for gradient consistency, ion mode vocabulary, matrix vocabulary, and required MS transition fields when ion mode is known.
- [x] Add an import preview report that summarizes missingness, invalid rows, and duplicate runs.

## Milestone C: Modeling And SOTA Path

- [x] Add grouped validation when enough rows exist; group by `inchikey`, `source_dataset`, and method family.
- [x] Add optional CatBoost/XGBoost support with graceful skip when packages are absent; LightGBM remains a future optional backend.
- [ ] Add Morgan fingerprint feature option in training CLI and compare with descriptor-only training. Feature option is implemented; full large-matrix comparison run remains.
- [x] Add applicability-domain metadata to the persisted bundle and use it in `ForwardPredictor._out_of_domain`.
- [ ] Add conformal interval reporting by source/matrix/column family once calibration rows exist.
- [x] Add a research note for future GNN/Transformer transfer learning architecture and required data volume.
- [x] Add optional dependency-gated graph and transformer embedding smoke paths with offline tests.

## Milestone D: Recommendation Engine Upgrade

- [x] Add score decomposition to recommendation outputs: RT fit, quality, runtime penalty, confidence, AD penalty.
- [x] Make search-space bounds configurable from a checked-in YAML/JSON settings file.
- [x] Add candidate constraints for available columns, solvent systems, pH range, flow range, temperature range, and max runtime.
- [x] Penalize out-of-domain candidates from trained bundle metadata.
- [x] Add tests for ranking stability and score decomposition.
- [x] Add optional inverse ML reranker trained on synthetic/proxy suitability labels and expose its score decomposition.

## Milestone E: GUI/API Release Polish

- [x] Add GUI import preview for literature-extracted and local-public processed CSVs.
- [x] Add Model Evaluation page views for source metrics, feature significance, AD flags, and uncertainty interval.
- [x] Add Training/Model Evaluation views for direct target readiness and inverse recommendation ML proxy metrics.
- [x] Add API tests for prediction, recommendation, and dataset browser endpoints.
- [ ] Smoke-test Streamlit and FastAPI locally.
- [ ] Add screenshots or placeholder screenshots only after GUI smoke passes.

## Milestone F: Release Discipline

- [ ] Run full verification in `.VERIFY`.
- [x] Update README with ReTiNA/METLIN/Kaggle and expanded quick-training commands.
- [x] Regenerate reports intentionally for the expanded local run.
- [x] Commit the expanded data/model-prep milestone.
- [x] Push `main`.

## Next Recommended Slice

Next high-value slice:

1. Run optional Morgan comparison artifact if CPU time is acceptable.
2. Add GUI/API release polish: local-public import preview, source metrics, AD flags, and uncertainty interval views.
3. Smoke-test Streamlit and FastAPI locally.
4. Run full tests, training, commit, push.

Recently completed continuation slices:

- Added Streamlit Model Evaluation panels for validation matrix, source-wise errors, AD flags, no-runtime feature importance, and runtime ablation outputs.
- Added Streamlit processed import preview for local public/literature CSVs with source counts, canonical coverage, missingness, and example rows.
- Added an artifact policy and local artifact manifest for the 213,941-row dataset and 188 MB trained bundle.
- Rebuilt the Russian PDF dashboard with source/method/column-family holdout metrics, feature importance, AD notes, and roadmap.
- Added direct-target readiness reporting, DL preparation manifests for pairwise/inverse tasks, proxy-trained inverse recommendation ML baselines, and dashboard/README integration.
- Added endpoint-level API tests for health, prediction, recommendation, and dataset browser behavior with mocked DB persistence.
